<main class="col-12 col-md-9 pull-md-3" id="main">
    <h1>Revenue by category</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Start &gt; Statistics</strong><strong>→ Type of statistic:</strong><strong>Revenue by category</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you have carried out changes, entered data or changed settings, click on the save icon in order to save your configuration before leaving the area.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_info_revenue_by_category">1. Info: Revenue by category</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This shows the <strong>revenue (gross) per category</strong> as well as the <strong>number of items</strong> that were sold during a certain time span. Default setting for the <strong>time span</strong>: the <strong>last 30 days</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_details_about_the_statistic">2. Details about the statistic</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>revenue (gross) per category</strong> and the <strong>number of items</strong> will be displayed for the selected <strong>time span</strong>. If no revenue is available, then the corresponding category will not be displayed. The <strong>number of sold items</strong> and the corresponding total <strong>revenue</strong> that was generated by this number of items will be displayed as <strong>information in a mouseover</strong> (see image 1). In this statistic you can see, e.g. how much revenue was generated in each of the different categories. If you change the time span, then you can also see how much revenue was generated in the different categories during a specific period of time.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
.
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="exampleblock">
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Exclusions</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Coupons</strong> will not be included in the statistical analysis. Neither will <strong>items</strong> that are <span class="underline">not linked to a category</span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Show details (mouseover)</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Point your <strong>cursor</strong> at one of the elements in the statistic in order to see <strong>details</strong> about that particular element.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Tip</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In image 1, you can see that <strong>46 items</strong> in the category <strong>Photo</strong> generated a total <strong>revenue</strong> of <strong>11244.42 Euros</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
